Furthermore, the proposed BioCoherence benchmark targeting directional validity and mechanistic feasibility adds diagnostic value beyond standard F1 metrics, supporting interpretability and generalization claims.

Although Idea 0's counterfactual causality analysis is innovative, similar perturbation-based probing exists in broader XAI literature; in contrast, refining AMR parses via KG feedback is a rarer and riskier idea, making it more likely to be perceived as a significant contribution if validated.

